<PropertyList>
  <scenario>
    <name>Bombable: (KSUN) 11 M1 tanks near Sun Valley</name>
    <description>This scenario puts a division of M1 Abrams tanks moving up the canyon towards Sun Valley, Idaho near Friedman Memorial Airport, KSUN.
       
The M1 Abrams are air-to-ground targets, you can damage them with bombs or heavy guns.  It is very challenging to track and target the tanks moving in the narrow confines of the canyon.

When you bomb and shoot the tanks they will slow down, finally catch fire, and then stop completely (to see the smoke and fire you must have Particles enabled in View/Rendering Options).

To damage the tanks takes a direct hit from a machine gun or heavy gun, or a close strike by a heavy bomb.

The tank formation starts near the northwest end of the runway at Friedman Memorial Airport in Halley, Idaho, and moves towards the northwest at approximately heading 340.

Install this scenario in the FlightGear/data/AI directory.

Any aircraft that shoots guns or drops bombs can damage the tanks.  The Fairchild A-10 Thunderbolt is a great choice - http://wiki.flightgear.org/index.php/Fairchild_A-10
		</description>
